BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Lw7IIVG_K83DJsAeT64Nf
SUMMARY:Contemporary Dance for Every Body
DTSTAMP:20260327T071602Z
DTSTART:20260409T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Class Overview\n\nWould you like to cultivate body awareness th
	rough movement? Explore a grounded and natural approach to moving your bod
	y\, led by a contemporary dance instructor.\n\nThrough floorwork\, movemen
	t sequences\, and phrasing\, this class cultivates body awareness. Explore
	 efficiency in movement transitions. Develop a deeper understanding of how
	 your body moves naturally in relation to the floor\, emphasizing organic 
	flow\, continuity\, spirality\, softness\, core engagement\, and the intel
	ligent use of gravity.\n\nOpen your mind and body through guided movement!
	 Explore points of support\, releasing tension\, and engaging the core to 
	facilitate flow and prevent injury. Movement principles will draw from con
	temporary dance and somatic practices\, encouraging dancers to move with c
	larity\, sensitivity\, and presence.\n\nThis class is for dancers\, actors
	\, physical theater artists\, yoga/movement practitioners\, and anyone int
	erested in exploring movement in their bodies -- no experience necessary. 
	Designed to be inclusive\, this class offers both accessibility and challe
	nge to movers at various levels and all backgrounds. \n\nLearning Objectiv
	es\n\nUnderstand and embody key principles of movement floorwork\, includi
	ng gravity\, spirality\, and core initiation.\n\nImprove movement continui
	ty and flow between levels \\(floor to standing and vice versa\\).\n\nExpl
	ore softness and efficiency through core engagement.\n\nIdentify and use a
	natomical points of support for safe and fluid movement.\n\nDevelop new da
	nce tools\n\nFeel more connected with the possibilities of your body in a 
	conscious way to live a more present\, healthy\, and aware life.\n\nWho Mi
	ght Enjoy This Class? \n\nAdult learners of all backgrounds \\(18\\+\\)\, 
	including dancers\, actors\, physical theater artists\, yoga/movement prac
	titioners\n\nAnyone interested in embodied movement practices.\n\nSome pri
	or movement or dance experience is helpful but not required. The class wil
	l be structured to accommodate varying levels of experience and physical a
	bility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/contemporary-danc
	e-for-every-body/18345436/2026-04-09T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/contemporary-dance-for-ev
	ery-body/18345436/2026-04-09T00
LOCATION:Seattle Central College Continuing Education\, 1701 Broadway\, Sea
	ttle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
